The song reached number one on the UK singles chart for two weeks in January 2000.
The song has sold 460,000 copies in the UK as stated by the Official UK Charts Company making the song one of the 14th best selling of 2000 in the UK.
"When a Woman" was released as the third single from Rise in June 2000.
"Should I Stay" was released as a single in 2000 and was the fourth and final single released from the Rise album.
In 2004, it was used in the second episode of the BBC drama serial Blackpool.
Gabrielle released her first greatest hits collection on 12 November 2001, entitled Dreams Can Come True, Greatest Hits Vol. 1.
The album achieved success in the UK where it was certified as a four times platinum seller and became the fifth best selling album of 2001.
The song reached number four in the UK and nine in Australia, making it her second biggest hit in the country and also the 37th highest selling single of 2001.
In New Zealand, the song was the tenth most successful single of 2001.
An arena tour of the United Kingdom followed in June 2002.
